OL,4,Cindustry scaremongering' on gambling
OL,5,Ctax
OL,7,FLast week, the chief executive of the
OL,8,FBGC appeared before the Treasury
OL,9,Fcommittee to answer MPs questions.
OL,11,FOn four occasions, Grainne Hurst
OL,12,Fdenied that gambling causes social
OL,13,Fharm, while acknowledging that a
OL,14,Fminority of people suffer harm through
OL,15,Fgambling.
OL,17,FHurst also argued that online gambling
OL,18,Fwas no more addictive than betting on
OL,19,Fhorse racing, a claim MPs have
OL,20,Frejected as "staggering".
